  />
  <p>The Encore ESP earns the top spot because it avoids the biggest compromise common in entry grinders: weak espresso control. Its adjustment design gives enough resolution in the fine range to dial better shots while still covering medium and coarse settings for filter brewing. For mixed-method households, that flexibility is hard to beat under $200.</p>
  <p>Daily workflow is straightforward: predictable dosing, manageable cleanup, and no unusual accessories required. If you want a grinder that stays useful even after your brewing skills improve, this is the safest long-term buy in this price band.</p>
  <p><CtaButton href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BW272XCV/ref=nosim?tag=coffee-site-20" external>Check Price on Amazon</CtaButton></p>

  <h3>2) OXO Brew Conical Burr Grinder</h3>
  <ProductCard
    title={products[1].name}
    image={{ src: products[1].image, alt: products[1].imageAlt, width: 500, height: 500 }}
    badge={products[1].badge}
